Compliance is not a one-time achievement but an ongoing lifecycle that requires continuous monitoring and improvement.

The lifecycle generally consists of:

* Requirement identification
* Policy implementation
* Continuous monitoring
* Compliance assessment
* Audit preparation
* Remediation
* Periodic review

For example, a healthcare provider must regularly verify that deployed resources continue to meet internal and external compliance requirements as new workloads are introduced.

A real-life use case is organizations preparing for annual compliance audits while maintaining continuous operational compliance throughout the year.

Continuous compliance reduces regulatory risks and strengthens customer confidence.
